# üìò Advanced Networking Labs

A collection of advanced, enterprise-grade networking and security labs built with Cisco Packet Tracer and Cisco IOS.  
These labs go far beyond introductory routing and ACL tasks ‚Äî each project demonstrates the ability to design, secure, and operate complex multi-layer networks.

This section is intended to showcase skills used in professional environments such as:

- Cybersecurity Analyst / SOC roles  
- Canadian Armed Forces Cyber Operator  
- Network Security Engineering  
- Infrastructure / NetOps positions  

These are **not** student-level labs.  
Each design models real-world architectures using multiple routers, switches, VLANs, DMZs, VPN tunnels, and layered security controls.

---

## üî• What These Labs Demonstrate

Each advanced lab is designed to prove hands-on capability in:

- Enterprise network segmentation  
- Perimeter security and DMZ design  
- Layer-3 switching  
- Multi-area OSPF routing  
- IPSec site-to-site VPN tunnels  
- Firewall-style extended ACL logic  
- High availability (HSRP)  
- SPAN/IDS monitoring & packet analysis  
- Multi-router, multi-switch enterprise topologies  

All labs include:

- Topology diagrams  
- Device/module requirements  
- IP addressing plans  
- Step-by-step configurations  
- Verification commands  
- Troubleshooting  
- Packet Tracer `.pkt` files  
- Screenshots & notes  

---

## üìÅ Advanced Lab Index

### **01 ‚Äì DMZ Firewall Design**  
`/advanced-networking/DMZ-Firewall-Design/`  
A complete perimeter architecture using an external router, DMZ zone, internal LAN, NAT, static NAT, and ACL-based firewalling. Includes isolation rules preventing DMZ‚ÜíLAN lateral movement.

---

### **02 ‚Äì Enterprise VLAN Segmentation**  
`/advanced-networking/Enterprise-VLAN-Segmentation/`  
Multiple VLANs (Finance, HR, Guest, Admin, Servers) using router-on-a-stick or L3 SVIs, trunk links, inter-VLAN routing, and ACL enforcement between departments.

---

### **03 ‚Äì OSPF Multi-Area Routing**  
`/advanced-networking/OSPF-MultiArea/`  
Enterprise OSPF with backbone (Area 0), additional areas, stub/totally stubby design, route summarization, and prefix filtering.

---

### **04 ‚Äì Site-to-Site IPSec VPN Tunnel**  
`/advanced-networking/Site-to-Site-VPN-IPSec/`  
Simulate secure encrypted communication between two remote sites using ISAKMP Phase 1, IPSec Phase 2, transform sets, crypto ACLs, and tunnel verification commands.

---

### **05 ‚Äì L3 Core Switching & ACL Security**  
`/advanced-networking/L3-Core-Switching/`  
Design a routed enterprise core switch with SVIs, server farm segmentation, access-layer uplinks, and ACL boundary rules.

---

### **06 ‚Äì High Availability (HSRP)**  
`/advanced-networking/High-Availability-HSRP/`  
Implement redundant default gateways with HSRP (active/standby), priority tuning, preemption, and failover testing.

---

### **07 ‚Äì IDS / SPAN Monitoring Lab**  
`/advanced-networking/IDS-SPAN-Monitoring/`  
Configure SPAN (port mirroring), attach a sniffer host, capture attack/malicious traffic, analyze packets, and apply mitigation using ACLs.

---

## üß∞ Tools Used

- Cisco Packet Tracer  
- Cisco IOS CLI  
- Optional: GNS3  
- Wireshark (SPAN labs)  
- Professional network diagrams  

---

## üéØ Purpose of This Section

This directory exists to demonstrate **enterprise-level networking skills**, not just academic exercises.

It shows you can:

- build real multi-router networks  
- secure boundaries using layered controls  
- design functional DMZ and VLAN architectures  
- configure enterprise routing protocols  
- operate and defend networks at a professional level  

These labs elevate the portfolio from ‚Äústudent projects‚Äù to **real-world engineering and cyber operations readiness**.
